  "text": "Found graceful shutdown handling across all three repositories:\n\n**Kubernetes/kubernetes**: The signal handler is registered in `signal.go` via `SetupSignalContext()` which listens for SIGINT/SIGTERM (defined per-platform in `signal_posix.go`). The graceful shutdown orchestration is in `genericapiserver.go`'s `RunWithContext()` method, which implements a sophisticated lifecycle signal system (`lifecycle_signals.go`) with ordered phases: ShutdownInitiated \u2192 AfterShutdownDelayDuration (default 70s) \u2192 PreShutdownHooksStopped \u2192 NotAcceptingNewRequest \u2192 InFlightRequestsDrained \u2192 HTTPServerStoppedListening. The `ShutdownTimeout` (default 60s) bounds how long to wait for in-flight requests. `secure_serving.go`'s `RunServer()` performs the actual `server.Shutdown(ctx)` with the timeout. Config options like `ShutdownSendRetryAfter` and `ShutdownWatchTerminationGracePeriod` control drain behavior.\n\n**Grafana/grafana**: Signal registration is in `cli.go`'s `listenToSystemSignals()` which listens for SIGINT/SIGTERM with a 30-second shutdown timeout context. It calls `Server.Shutdown()` in `server.go`, which shuts down background services via a manager adapter. The gRPC server (`service.go`) has its own graceful shutdown with `GracefulShutdownTimeout` (configurable, default 10s in `setting_grpc.go`) \u2014 it attempts `GracefulStop()` and falls back to `Stop()` on timeout.\n\n**Prometheus/prometheus**: Signal registration is in `cmd/prometheus/main.go` using `oklog/run.Group` actor model. The termination handler listens for `os.Interrupt`/`SIGTERM` and triggers orderly shutdown of all actors. The web handler (`web.go`) runs an HTTP server and calls `httpSrv.Shutdown()` when its context is canceled. Cleanup ordering is managed by the run.Group: when any actor exits, all interrupt functions fire \u2014 stopping scrape manager before closing TSDB, stopping rule manager, etc.",
